This paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it discusses the implementation of a program execution monitor for the Mercury programming language. It may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it discusses the development of software visualization tools. Additionally, the paper mentions the generation of graphical abstractions, which could fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of a general-purpose primitive that can be used with any programming language, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
